9:00A Start Time

title: Palmer's Sand Springs Criterium - OK Age-Graded State Championship
description: Palmer and Team Tom's Bicycles are bringing the Palmer Sand Springs Criterium back this year and will also be hosting the Oklahoma Age-Graded State Championship. You don't want to miss it.
course: Technical course with short, challenging climbs and a fast sprint finish located in downtown Sand Springs. The course will be closed to traffic.  Wheel pit will be along town triangle and accessible from two points. Wheels in Wheels out.  Start/Finish is located at N. McKinley and E. Broadway in Sand Springs.
registration: Race day registration opens at 7:00am and will be open all day per fees below.  Registration closes 15 minutes before each race.  $15 for each additional race.  One-day and annual USAC licenses will be on sale. Online registration at www.usacycling.org **Race Day Registration increases by $10.00. Online registration closes midnight May 15th.
notes:
All proceeds from Palmer’s Sand Springs Criterium are donated to Palmer’s Continuum of Care.

Race will be held rain or shine.  USA Cycling rules apply.  All racers are required to have a current USAC license or purchase a license on race day.  Parents or guardians must sign entries for riders under 18.  Promoters reserve the right to combine classes, cancel classes, adjust course length and start times.  Entry Fee includes $3 insurance surcharge and $0.75 Local Association surcharge.  



State Championship Information 

•	Palmer’s Sand Springs Criterium is hosting Age Based Oklahoma Championships only. State Championship Jerseys will be offered in the age groups listed below. Ages are based on the racing age of your 2013 USACycling license. You must race your age group and are only eligible for championship and prize money/awards for your age group. 
•	Out of state riders and racers using a one day license are not eligible for State Champions, but may race for prize money/awards. 
•	All races not listed below will not be awarded State Championship Jerseys State Championship Categories Men 30-39, 40-49, 50-59 and 60+ Men U23 (age 19-23) Juniors (both women and men) 10-14, 15-16 and 17-18 Women 40+.

Kids Race Information
Kids race is for anyone under the age of 9.  Parents must sign a waiver but there is no charge.  Kids will do a very short section of the race course.  Everyone will get a ribbon or medal at the finish.
directions:
From Tulsa:  US 412 East toward Enid/Sand Springs 6.1 miles, Exit Adams Rd onto 2nd street, Follow signs to event parking.
From OKC:  Exit I-44 at Exit #215/Ok97 toward Sand Springs/Sapulpa, left on N 9th ST [Ok-97] follow for 8.6 miles to 2nd street.  Right on 2nd to McKinley.

title: Red River Shootout: One Hundred Degrees of Purgatory
Bixby Bicycles - Oklahoma State Time Trial
Endurance 69
description: Six-hour endurance mountain bike race.  Laps are 9 miles on single track mountain bike trail with some paved connector sections.
course: Course begins in downtown Medicine Park, OK and continues around the south and west sides of Lake Lawtonka.
registration: On –site registration will be held the day of the race beginning at 8:00am at Base Camp Adventure Outfitters in Medicine Park. On- site registration will end 30 minutes prior to start time! Helmets are required when rider is on the bike. On-line race fee is $40 for single and $80 for team.  On-site registration is $5 more than listed prices per rider.  Entry fee includes event T-shirt.  To avoid waiting in line on race day online registration is highly recommended and available at www.usacycling.org
notes: There will be five classes: Men's Open, Women's Open, Men's Team, Women's Team, and Mixed Team.  No age classes.  Riders must have an annual or one-day USAC MTB license.
directions: From I-44, take the Medicine Park exit and go 4 miles west.  Turn right and take East Lake Drive 1.5 miles to Base Camp Adventure Outfitters.

title: Family Fat Tire Festival

address.street: Lake Thunderbird State Park, 13101 Alameda Dr

description:
Every fall, the Family Fat Tire Festival takes place on a Saturday 10 am -2 pm out at Lake Thunderbird State park Clear Bay mountain Bike Trails, off Highway 9 (14 miles East of I-35). Norman.

The Family Fat Tire Festival is a FREE annual event that is presented by Team Phoenix racing, along with Norman Regional Health System and Bike one. We make this a family friendly community event, where they get to experience bicycle trail riding that is fun for the whole family at one of Oklahoma’s premier mountain bike trails, Clear Bay at Lake Thunderbird in Norman, Oklahoma.

We teach bike safety awareness, give guided bike rides on marked trails with a lead and sweep team members and much more.
directions: Lake Thunderbird State park Clear Bay mountain Bike Trails, off Highway 9 (14 miles East of I-35). Norman.

title: Rock the Mohawk CX
description: Rock the Mohawk CX race is hosted by Team Tom's Bicycles at Mohawk Park on 10/25/15 this year. It's always a party. Don't miss it.
course: Excellent course with a little bit of everything. 200m asphalt start, grass, dirt, short single-track section, stairs, barriers and chicanes. Not a bad deal.
registration: Please register online at USAC. Registration closes 10/23/2015 at 10PM MST. On-site registration will be available and will open by 8:15am for an additional $10 and closes 15 minutes prior to each event. Race a second race for $20.
notes: Course will be open for pre-ride approximately 10 minutes prior to races. OKGP call-ups will be utilized at start. Event flyer at usacycling.org and www.rockthemohawk.com.
